The paper deals with image analysis and segmentation, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of geometric criteria and cut-line for separation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a database, which suggests that it may belong to the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with a specific application of chromosome analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of data structures (cs.DS) for efficient storage and retrieval of genetic data.
